  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='black' class='header'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>DETAILS ON KILLING TRUMPY IRONTOE</font>, By Hrothgarr shadetree</b><br><br>If you have adventured near Qeynos long, you should be able to tell the Corrupt Guards form the Good ones, so make sure when you kill Trumpy, there are only good guards around - they should leave you alone.  Also, make sure you are out of sight of Bruno Barstomper because he is tough (cons red at lvl 25) and GMs have told me there is no way of raising your faction with him.  Fortunately, this is on the edge of Qeynos, so if you are KoS there, you can still use most of the city.
Another person to look out for is Danaria Holland - an Erudite enchantress (how can you tell with chanters what race they are?) who I have never had problems with, but I have seen her attack others when Trumpy ran past her.  She uses a Lvl 20 pet and cons blue to my Lvl 24 chanter.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>HOW TO GET HAMMER</font>, By Aieny</b><br><br>This quest is really easy...but long, particular if you can't teleport and don't have a friend who will do it for you.  First, go to South Qeynos in the Fish's Ale tavern.  There you will find Thrumpy(?) Irontoe.  Buy about four honey meads from the bartender, then hail the dwarf.  He will keep asking for a drink (the honey mead) until he is satisfied that you are his friend.<P>
  At this point, he starts mentioning names.  Follow the conversation, asking about the names, and eventually he walks out of the bar.  Follow him, and when you get to a secluded part of town (well away from the bar), kill him.  He is approx level 6-7, so killing him shouldn't be hard.  Just be sure to root him in case he decides to get help.  Once he is dead, loot the Dwarf Head from his corpse and go to Kaladim.<P>

Once in Kaladim, go to the Warrior guild and find a guy named Byzar Bloodforge.  You must have amiable con with him or this won't work.  Give him the head, and in return you get experience and the Bloodforge Hammer.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
